&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rheumatology Infusion Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 17 hours (over 2 days)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Band 5 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This rewarding post is open to Nurses with at least 1 year Band 5 experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the dynamic Rheumatology team at Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust. The service provides, primarily for patients with inflammatory arthropathies with emphasis on a multidisciplinary approach and patient centred care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key role is to provide patient centred care for those attending as Rheumatology day patients for I.V therapy. The role is also to provide support guidance and leadership to the Nursing assistants and Bank nurses also working in the Infusion Unit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;strong&gt;Please refer to Job Description for personal specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Alison Kent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Rheumatology Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address alisonkent1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01722 429137&lt;/p&gt;
